<TITLE> Hafizuddin takes swipe at govt </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 20 (bdnews24.com)Reformist BNP leader Hafizuddin Ahmed Tuesday asked the caretaker government to stop its fresh drive to arrest political leaders and to pay attention to creating a proper environment for the polls. The comment makes his first public criticism of the caretaker government, which came two days after former BNP secretary general Abdul Mannan Bhuiyan landed in jail in the GATCO scam case. Expressing doubt about the success of probable dialogue, Hafizuddin said: "The government should not have arranged dialogue with political parties. It put the government in a double bind." Speaking at a press briefing at his Banani home, he said: "If the dialogue is not held with two top political partiesBNP and the Awami Leaguethe talks will not be successful." bdnew
